<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="687" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18058</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Representative <persName type="to">Rodgers</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>69. Department informed Generals Scott and Obregon have reached
                            satisfactory agreement and that result of their conference has been
                            referred to General Carranza for his approval which, according to
                            General Obregon, is still being awaited.</p>
                        <p>Discreetly ascertain and telegraph General Carranza’s attitude in matter
                            soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>